description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a highly Specialised cardiac physiologist trained in echocardiography to join our team. Suitable candidates will be expected to provide clinical expertise at a higher level with a focus in echocardiography including TTE, TOE, Contrast, Valve Surveillance and GUCH.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You should be able to work autonomously with a focus on patient centered care. We work actively with our consultants to address patient issues and the post holder would be expected to participate in our weekly MDT.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We require an individual who is also well trained in other areas of Cardiology to assist with providing services within the department such as ECG, ambulatory monitoring, ETT, Brady Pacing follow up /implant, ILR follow up/implant and cardiac catheterisation as required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Further information regarding any of the post can be obtained by calling the department on the number provided.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Suitable candidates should possess a BSc in Clinical Physiology, &lt;span&gt;BSE accreditation or equivalent &lt;/span&gt;and also should be eligible for RCCP/AHCS registration. Evidence of CPD focusing on echocardiography would be beneficial and our department actively encourages attendance at meetings/course to keep up to date with the developments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
